               <msContents>
                  <summary>The letter fragment on recto contains the basmalla followed by one more line of writing. The abbrogated character of this text and the line in the right upper margin at a 90 degree angle to the rest of the text belonging to an earlier text suggest that the three lines might be pen trials.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Recto (perpendicular to fibres) contains 3 lines and has been cut out off a larger papyrus.</note>
                     <note type="general">Verso contains an account and pen trials in Arabic. See nyu.apis.5360.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar-Arab">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
